## Overview
FlexServe simplifies discovery, comparison, and booking of services on a single platform. It provides provider listings, availability tracking, time-slot booking, online payments, reviews, and admin controls — enhanced with AI for smarter matching and fraud mitigation.

## Problem Statement
Many service bookings are handled manually via social media, messaging apps, or phone calls, causing miscommunication, double bookings, schedule management problems, and trust/security concerns. Users lack a centralized, intelligent platform that streamlines booking and decision-making.

## Key Features
- User registration & profile management (customers & providers)
- Provider listings with detailed profiles and availability calendars
- Time-slot based booking system with double-book prevention and buffer times
- Online payments (full payment or deposit) and refund handling
- Reviews and ratings system
- Booking history and receipts
- Admin dashboard for user, booking and transaction management
- Reporting tools for platform activity and trends

## AI Features
- Smart Matching (mandatory): Recommends providers using user preferences (budget, service type, location, availability, past behavior) and learns from interactions to improve recommendations.
- Fraud & Fake ID Detection: Detects suspicious booking patterns and inconsistent profile information to reduce scams and fake accounts.

## User Roles
- Customer: Search, filter, book, pay, review
- Service Provider: Manage profile, availability, accept/reject bookings, view history
- Admin: Approve providers, moderate content, manage disputes, run reports

## Functional Requirements (summary)
- Secure registration and authentication with role-based access control
- Search & filters (service, price, rating, availability)
- Booking engine (time-slot management, conflict prevention, reschedule/cancel)
- Payment gateway integration (multiple methods), deposit/full payment workflows
- Reviews & rating
- Administrative controls and moderation
- AI modules for recommendation and fraud detection

## Non-functional Requirements
- Performance: fast, responsive search & booking, concurrency-safe scheduling
- Availability: high uptime with planned maintenance windows
- Security: protect personal and payment data, fraud controls, secure authentication
- Reliability: transactional integrity for bookings and payments, backups
- Scalability: support growing users and bookings

## Information Gathering & Requirement Analysis
Requirements were gathered via stakeholder meetings (2 online, 1 face-to-face), questionnaires (Google Forms), and interviews. Users confirmed reliance on manual booking, concerns about scams and double-bookings, and positive reception to the proposed AI features and booking controls.

## Suggested Architecture & Data Flow
- Frontend: web or mobile clients (React / React Native / Vue)
- Backend: RESTful or GraphQL API (Node/Express, Django, or similar)
- Database: relational DB for users/bookings (Postgres/MySQL)
- Payments: integrate with FPX, card processors, e-wallet providers
- AI services: separate microservice(s) for Smart Matching and Fraud Detection (could use Python, TensorFlow/PyTorch or cloud ML services)
- Admin dashboard and reporting
- DFD / Context Diagram: produce Context Diagram → Level 0 → Child diagrams to model booking flows, payments, and AI interactions (not included here)

## Suggested Tech Stack (example)
- Frontend: React / Next.js or Vue
